<section id="services-hero-532"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-landscape-maintenance-1.jpeg" height="775" width="1920" fetchpriority="high"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-card"><div class="cs-heading-group"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Heads. Valves. Leaks. Controllers. Blowouts.</span><h1 class="cs-title">Sprinkler Repair in <span class="cs-color">Las Cruces, NM</span></h1></div><p class="cs-text">Broken head, soggy lawn, zone that won’t turn on, water bill out of control? We diagnose and repair sprinkler systems across Las Cruces and the Mesilla Valley. Same-week service, written estimate before any work, and workmanship guarantee on parts we install. 19 years in business. 500+ projects.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Schedule a Diagnosis</a> <a href="tel:575-635-8883" class="cs-phone-button"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></section><section id="services-intro-109"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-right"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-left"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><img alt="Drip irrigation and sprinkler repair work by Brainard's Greenscapes in Las Cruces, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-drip-irrigation.jpeg" height="604" width="480" loading="lazy"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> What We Repair</span><h2 class="cs-title">Full-Service Sprinkler System Repair</h2><p class="cs-text">A failing sprinkler system can waste hundreds of gallons a month while half your lawn goes brown. We track down the actual cause, whether that is a cracked head, a stuck valve, an underground leak, or a controller that lost its schedule. Every visit starts with a diagnosis and a written estimate, so you know exactly what is wrong and what the fix costs before we lift a shovel.</p><ul class="cs-bullets"><li>Sprinkler head repair and replacement on every common brand.</li><li>Valve repair, solenoid replacement, and diaphragm rebuilds.</li><li>Underground leak detection and main-line repair.</li><li>Drip system repair, clogged emitters, and pressure regulator swaps.</li><li>Smart and traditional controller troubleshooting and reprogramming.</li><li>Seasonal blowout, spring start-up, and tune-ups.</li></ul><div class="cs-button-group"><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Schedule a Repair Visit</a> <a href="tel:575-635-8883" class="cs-phone-button"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/icon-irrigation-56.webp" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Sprinkler Head Repair</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Cracked, stuck, tilted, or leaking heads. Hunter, Rain Bird, Toro, and Orbit pop-ups stocked on the truck.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-maintenance.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Sprinkler Valve Repair</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Stuck-on or stuck-off zones, bad solenoids, torn diaphragms, debris in the seat. Rebuild or swap, your call.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-xeriscaping.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Leak Detection</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Soggy spots, runaway meter, unexplained bill spike. Pressure tests and zone-by-zone runs pinpoint the leak.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscape-design.svg" height="56" width="56" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Controller Troubleshooting</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Lost schedules, dead displays, no-WiFi smart controllers. Repair, reprogram, or upgrade as needed.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-process-148"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> What to Expect</span><h2 class="cs-title">Our 4-Step Sprinkler Repair Process</h2></div><div class="cs-grid-wrap"><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Schedule a Visit</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Call or book online. We schedule with a window so you are not waiting all day. Same-week service for most calls.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Diagnose</h3><p class="cs-item-text">We run every zone, check pressure, listen for leaks, open valve boxes, and check the controller. We find the actual cause before recommending a fix.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Written Estimate</h3><p class="cs-item-text">You see the price for parts and labor before we lift a shovel. Most repairs are approved and finished the same visit.</p></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-lightbulb.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Fix &amp; Verify</h3><p class="cs-item-text">We make the repair, run every affected zone, and walk you through the result. Workmanship guarantee on every part we install.</p></li></ul><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-down.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-1"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-up.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-2"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/leaf-down.svg" height="184" width="168" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-vine cs-vine-3"></div></div></section><section id="services-signs-870"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Warning Signs</span><h2 class="cs-title">Is Your Sprinkler System Not Working Right?</h2><p class="cs-text">A sprinkler system has a way of failing slowly. By the time the symptoms are obvious, gallons of water have already gone down the wrong path. Any of these is a reason to call.</p></div><div class="cs-button-group"><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Schedule a Diagnosis</a> <a href="tel:575-635-8883" class="cs-phone-button"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div><ul class="cs-signs"><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Sprinkler Head Leaking from the Top</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">A head that drips when the zone is off is almost always low-head drainage. We add check valves or swap in pop-ups with built-in check valves and the runoff stops.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Broken Sprinkler Heads</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Cracked, stuck, sunken, or tilted heads waste water and leave dry patches. We carry every common pop-up on the truck and match precipitation so the zone stays even.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">A Zone Won’t Turn On (or Won’t Turn Off)</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">A zone that fails to fire or refuses to close is almost always a stuck solenoid, a torn diaphragm, or debris in the valve seat. Most are a one-visit rebuild or swap.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Soggy Spots and Runaway Meter</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">If the lawn stays wet days after a run or your meter spins with every zone off, you have an underground leak. We pressure-test and zone-isolate to find it.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Water Bill Up With No Explanation</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">A spike in your bill usually means a hidden leak, a stuck valve, or a controller running an old summer schedule into the fall. All three are diagnosable in one visit.</p></li><li class="cs-sign"><h3 class="cs-sign-title">Sprinkler System Not Working After Power Blip</h3><p class="cs-sign-text">Older controllers lose their schedule when power flickers. We reprogram, restore the city-ordinance schedule, and verify every zone before we leave.</p></li></ul></div><img alt="Healthy lawn restored by Brainard's Greenscapes sprinkler repair in Las Cruces" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-sod-2.jpeg" height="1006" width="616" loading="lazy"></div></section><section id="services-region-450"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Common Repairs</span><h2 class="cs-title">The Sprinkler Repairs We See Most in Las Cruces</h2></div><div class="cs-body"><p class="cs-text">Nineteen years of repair calls in Las Cruces come down to a small set of recurring problems. Here is what we fix most weeks of the year.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Head repair and replacement:</strong> cracked, stuck, sunken, or tilted pop-ups; broken risers; mismatched nozzles. We swap in matching Hunter, Rain Bird, Toro, or Orbit heads and re-set precipitation across the zone.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Valve repair:</strong> bad solenoids, torn diaphragms, debris under the seat, broken bonnets. We rebuild or swap the valve at the manifold and verify the zone closes cleanly.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Underground leak detection:</strong> soggy lawn, lifted sod, unexplained meter run. Pressure tests and zone runs isolate the leak; we dig only the spot we need to fix it.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Drip system repair:</strong> clogged emitters from hard Las Cruces water, cut tubing from edging or shovel work, blown filters, missing pressure regulators. We clean, replace, and add the parts that should have been there from the start.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Controller and timer repair:</strong> failed displays, lost schedules, smart controllers that dropped WiFi, controllers that survived a freeze in the wrong location. Repair, reprogram, or upgrade depending on age.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Backflow preventer repair:</strong> cracked bonnets, leaking test cocks, freeze damage. Code-required protection for keeping irrigation water out of your drinking lines.</p><p class="cs-text"><strong>Seasonal service:</strong> fall blowout (compressor air through every zone), spring start-up, summer scheduling tune-ups. Keep this up and you avoid most of the calls above.</p><a href="/contact/" class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button">Book a Repair Visit</a></div><img alt="Sprinkler system repair work by Brainard's Greenscapes in Las Cruces, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-misc-2.jpeg" height="904" width="440" loading="lazy"></div></section><section id="services-why-353"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern.jpeg" height="1840" width="1920" loading="lazy"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Why Choose Us</span><h2 class="cs-title">Why Las Cruces Trusts Brainard’s for Sprinkler Repair</h2><p class="cs-intro">A repair done right starts with finding the actual cause, not the easy guess. Pressure tests, valve-box opens, and zone-by-zone runs catch the small stuff before it costs hundreds of gallons. Honest pricing, written estimates, and parts that match what is already in the ground.</p></div><div class="cs-gallery" aria-hidden="true"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-landscape-maintenance-2.webp" height="594" width="460" loading="lazy"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-21.jpeg" height="439" width="330" loading="lazy"></div><ul class="cs-feature-list"><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Same-Week Service</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Most repair calls scheduled within the week. Scheduled windows so you are not waiting around all day for the truck.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Truck Stocked With Common Parts</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Hunter, Rain Bird, Toro, and Orbit heads, valves, solenoids, fittings, and pipe on every truck. Most repairs are finished in one visit.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Written Estimate Before Work</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">You see parts and labor pricing before we dig. No surprises at the end. Approve in the field and we keep going.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Workmanship Guarantee</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Our installation labor on every repair is guaranteed for as long as you own the home. Plus full manufacturer warranties on the parts.</p></li></ul><a href="/contact/" class="cs-quote-button">Schedule a Repair</a></div></section><section id="services-pricing-219"><div class="cs-container"><article class="cs-price-card"><h2 class="cs-price-title">Sprinkler Repair Cost in Las Cruces</h2><span class="cs-price-label">Typical Range</span> <span class="cs-price-amount"><span class="cs-price-symbol">$</span>125–$850</span><p class="cs-price-text">Sprinkler repair cost in Las Cruces typically runs $125 to $250 for a service-call diagnosis plus a head or two. Sprinkler valve repair and zone troubleshooting run $200 to $450. Underground leak repair and main-line work runs $350 to $850 depending on access and depth. Controller troubleshooting starts at $125. Every visit includes a written estimate before any work begins.</p><ul class="cs-price-bullets"><li>On-site diagnosis and written estimate, every visit.</li><li>No surprise charges. Approve in the field and we keep going.</li><li>Workmanship guarantee on installed parts.</li></ul><a href="/contact/" class="cs-price-link">Schedule a Repair Visit <svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></a></article><article class="cs-diff-card"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern.jpeg" height="605" width="572" loading="lazy"><h2 class="cs-diff-title">The Brainard’s Difference</h2><ul class="cs-diff-list"><li class="cs-diff-item"><span class="cs-diff-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3 V21"></path><path d="M8 8 H16"></path></svg></span><div class="cs-diff-body"><h3 class="cs-diff-name">Faith-Centered</h3><p class="cs-diff-text">Honest diagnosis, real cause, fair price. We do not pad invoices or sell parts you do not need.</p></div></li><li class="cs-diff-item"><span class="cs-diff-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 3 L20 6 V12 C20 16.5 16.5 20 12 21 C7.5 20 4 16.5 4 12 V6 Z"></path></svg></span><div class="cs-diff-body"><h3 class="cs-diff-name">Workmanship Guarantee</h3><p class="cs-diff-text">The labor on every repair is guaranteed for as long as you own the home. Plus manufacturer warranties on every part installed.</p></div></li><li class="cs-diff-item"><span class="cs-diff-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2 C8 2 5 5 5 9 C5 14 12 22 12 22 C12 22 19 14 19 9 C19 5 16 2 12 2 Z"></path><circle cx="12" cy="9" r="2.5"></circle></svg></span><div class="cs-diff-body"><h3 class="cs-diff-name">Locally Rooted</h3><p class="cs-diff-text">Las Cruces water, soil, and pressure quirks are baked into how we diagnose. We have seen it before, in this city, this season.</p></div></li></ul></article></div></section><section id="services-local-360"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Repair &amp; Reprogram</span><h2 class="cs-title">Repaired and Programmed to the Las Cruces Ordinance</h2><p class="cs-text">Every repair visit ends with the controller programmed to the city schedule. If the previous owner or installer left it on a non-compliant schedule, we fix that too.</p></div><ul class="cs-local-list"><li><strong>Address parity:</strong> even-numbered addresses water Tue / Thu / Sat. Odd-numbered water Wed / Fri / Sun.</li><li><strong>No watering on Mondays.</strong> We confirm Monday is locked out before we leave.</li><li><strong>April 1–Sept 30:</strong> no watering between 10 a.m. and 6 p.m. We move runs to pre-dawn or post-dusk.</li><li><strong>Rain skip &amp; seasonal adjust:</strong> verified working on smart controllers, set manually on traditional timers.</li><li><strong>Backflow preventer:</strong> code-required for outdoor irrigation. We test and repair as part of the diagnosis.</li><li><strong>Water-waste hotline:</strong> the city accepts reports at 575-528-4444. A correctly repaired and programmed system keeps you off that radar.</li></ul><p class="cs-text cs-text-footer">Source: <a href="https://lascruces.gov/property/utilities/utility-services/water-conservation/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Las Cruces Utilities Water Conservation Program</a>.</p></div></section><section id="service-areas-825"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><aside class="cs-info-card"><div class="cs-info-head"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <svg height="10" viewBox="0 0 48 10" width="48" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.4" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"><path d="M2 5 H42"></path><path d="M36 1 L42 5 L36 9"></path></svg> Where We Service</span><h2 class="cs-title">Las Cruces &amp; the Mesilla Valley</h2></div><div class="cs-info-body"><p class="cs-text">We repair sprinkler systems throughout Las Cruces and the Mesilla Valley, roughly within 30 miles of our office.</p><ul class="cs-locations"><li><a href="/service-areas/las-cruces-nm/">Sprinkler Repair in Las Cruces, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/mesilla-nm/">Sprinkler Repair in Mesilla, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/dona-ana-nm/">Sprinkler Repair in Doña Ana, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/sonoma-ranch-nm/">Sprinkler Repair in Sonoma Ranch, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/picacho-hills-nm/">Sprinkler Repair in Picacho Hills, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/east-mesa-nm/">Sprinkler Repair in East Mesa, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/anthony-nm/">Sprinkler Repair in Anthony, NM</a></li><li><a href="/service-areas/sunland-park-nm/">Sprinkler Repair in Sunland Park, NM</a></li></ul></div><img alt="Brainard's Greenscapes sprinkler repair in Las Cruces" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-landscape-maintenance-3.jpeg" height="130" width="428" loading="lazy"><div class="cs-office"><h3 class="cs-office-heading">Our Office Location</h3><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Brainard's+Greenscapes/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x3c69d063ef4f24?sa=X&amp;ved=1t:2428&amp;ictx=111" class="cs-office-address" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Las Cruces, NM </a><span class="cs-office-underline" aria-hidden="true"></span> <a href="/service-areas/" class="cs-office-button">View All Service Areas</a></div></aside><div class="cs-map"><iframe allowfullscreen="" height="934" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade" src="https://www.google.com/maps?q=Las%20Cruces+NM&amp;output=embed" title="Map of Las Cruces, NM service area" width="960"></iframe></div></div></section><section id="testimonials-515" class="cs-reviews-carousel"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern.jpeg" height="1072" width="1920" loading="lazy"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Testimonials</span><h2 class="cs-title">Let’s Talk About Your Outdoor Vision</h2></div><div class="cs-controls"><button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-prev" aria-label="Previous reviews" type="button" data-reviews-prev=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M15 18l-6-6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button> <button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-next" aria-label="Next reviews" type="button" data-reviews-next=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M9 6l6 6-6 6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button></div></div><ul class="cs-card-group" data-reviews-track=""><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">David was incredibly knowledgeable and helpful. He patiently answered all of my questions about the plants and trees around my home and provided valuable insights into the issues I was facing. His friendly demeanor and expertise made the experience enjoyable and informative. I highly recommend him</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Alexis Silva</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103948667181155023139/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">We had a great experience with David. We used him for one of our rental properties in Las Cruces and will definitely be using him again for the next one. Everything from start to finish was professional and timely. Highly recommend.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Travis Boyle</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108997149124684397289/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard's Greenscapes recently revamped my backyard with rock landscaping. I couldn't be happier with how the project turned out. From start to finish David's team was professional, punctual, and courteous. They helped me select the the right materials and offered additional design ideas. The quality of work was EXCELLENT. I highly recommend David's team to all homeowners in Las Cruces looking for reliable landscaping company. The picture below is of my backyard 1 year later and there is still no weeds! I can't think Braindard's Greenscapes enough.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Matthew Lee</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112275232644298872770/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">I had a sprinkler emergency and David came out immediately; found an effective solution to get me through until the major repairs could be made; and took care to make sure my house wasn't without water in the meantime. I am so grateful for his kindness and professionalism. He demonstrated considerable expertise and decisive decision making that got me through this emergencies with minimal stress. He is trustworthy and will be the first one I'll call on any future sprinkler needs.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Jennifer Wees-Schkade</span> <span class="cs-role">2 years ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113879630740524577871/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" role="img" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard’s Greenscapes is a top notch business. I have called on them on several occasions to fix issues with my irrigation system and for new projects. David, the owner, is a sincere, honest individual, who cares about his business and his customers. His employees are also kind and always professional. They are punctual and complete the job as promised and clean up after they are done. I am very pleased with David and his company and have recommended him to my neighbor, who is also a widow because I know he is honest and will not take advantage of her. David is a good guy and I recommend that you give him a call and see for yourself.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">George Rodriguez</span> <span class="cs-role">6 years ago</span></div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113926776793747685994/reviews" class="cs-google-link" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li></ul></div></section><section id="faq-506"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> FAQ</span><h2 class="cs-title">Sprinkler Repair FAQs</h2></div><ul class="cs-faq-list"><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How much does sprinkler repair cost in Las Cruces?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Sprinkler repair in Las Cruces typically runs $125 to $250 for a service-call diagnosis plus a head or two. Valve repair and zone troubleshooting run $200 to $450. Underground leaks and main-line repairs run $350 to $850 depending on how deep the line is and whether we have to dig under hardscape. Every visit includes a written estimate before any work begins.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How do I find a leak in my sprinkler system?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Look for soggy spots, unusually green patches, lifted sod, or a water meter that keeps spinning when every zone is off. Those are the classic underground-leak signs. We use pressure tests and zone-by-zone runs to isolate exactly where the line is leaking, then dig only the spot we need to fix it. Most leak repairs are a same-day job.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Why is my sprinkler head leaking water when off?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>A sprinkler head that leaks water when the zone is off is almost always low-head drainage. Water in the lateral pipe drains out through the lowest head on the zone after the valve closes. We fix it by installing check valves in the affected heads or swapping in pop-ups with built-in check valves. The repair is quick and stops the runoff for good.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How do I repair a broken sprinkler head?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Replacing a sprinkler head is straightforward when you can see the threaded riser. Turn off the zone, unscrew the broken pop-up, clean the riser threads, and screw in a matching head. The harder cases are tilted or sunken heads, broken risers below grade, or non-matching nozzles that throw off the zone’s coverage. We carry every common Hunter, Rain Bird, and Toro pop-up on the truck and can match precipitation rates so the zone stays even after the swap.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Why is my sprinkler system not working?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Most full-system failures trace back to one of four things: the controller lost its program after a power blip, the master valve or backflow shut off, a single zone wire pulled loose, or a stuck solenoid is keeping the whole system in one zone. We diagnose all four in one service visit. Most no-water calls are fixed the same day.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Can you fix a sprinkler valve that won’t turn off?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. A zone that won’t shut off is usually a stuck solenoid, a torn diaphragm, or a piece of debris under the valve seat. We diagnose at the valve box, rebuild or replace the solenoid and diaphragm, flush the line, and verify the zone closes cleanly. Most stuck-valve calls are a one-visit fix.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Do you offer sprinkler system blowout service for winter?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. Las Cruces winters are mild but a few hard freezes a year can crack pipes, split valves, and damage backflow preventers. We offer fall blowout (compressor air pushed through every zone), spring start-up, and seasonal controller adjustments. Most homeowners book the package together so they hand off the system once a year.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How long does a sprinkler repair visit take?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Most sprinkler repair visits in Las Cruces take 60 to 120 minutes from arrival to test-run. Head replacements and valve rebuilds are usually 60 minutes. Underground leak repair runs longer because we have to find the leak, dig the access, and restore the trench. We schedule with a window so you are not waiting all day.</p></div></details></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-related-184"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Related Services</span><h2 class="cs-title">Pair Sprinkler Repair with These Services</h2><p class="cs-tex